
AIM: To explore and understand the use of basic Flutter widgets such as Text, Image, Container, Column, and Row.

DESCRIPTION:

In Flutter, everything is a widget â€” including layout elements, text, images, and buttons.
Widgets describe what the UI should look like and how it should behave.
Common Flutter Widgets:
Widget   -	Description
Text       -	Displays a string of text on the screen.
Image    -	Displays an image from assets, network, or file.
Container	- A box model widget that can have padding, margin, border, and color.
Column   -	Arranges widgets vertically.


	Row-Arranges widgets horizontally.
PROGRAM:

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'Flutter Widget Demo',
      home: Scaffold(
        appBar: AppBar(
          title: Text('Flutter Basic Widgets'),
          backgroundColor: Colors.teal,
        ),
        body: Center(
          child: Column(
            mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
            children: [
              // Text Widget
              Text(
                'Hello, Flutter!',
                style: TextStyle(fontSize: 24, fontWeight: FontWeight.bold),
              ),

              SizedBox(height: 20),

              // Image Widget (from network)
              Image.network(
                'https://flutter.github.io/assets-for-api-docs/assets/widgets/owl.jpg',
                width: 150,
              ),

              SizedBox(height: 20),

              // Container Widget
              Container(
                height: 100,
                width: 200,
                decoration: BoxDecoration(
                  color: Colors.orange,
                  borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(15),
                  border: Border.all(color: Colors.black, width: 2),
                ),
                child: Center(
                  child: Text(
                    'I am inside a Container!',
                    style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 16),
                  ),
                ),
              ),
            ],
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}


